install new linux kernel
linux driver

1. cd /usr/src
2. download kernel
ex:
wget http://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v2.6/linux-2.6.35.7.tar.bz2

3. tar xjf linux-2.6.18.3.tar.bz2
4. create link
ex:
ln -s linux-2.6.35.7 linux

5. add patch (optional)
under /usr/src/linux
ex:
for bz2 patch
bzip2 -dc /usr/src/patch.bz2 | patch -p1 --dry-run
bzip2 -dc /usr/src/patch.bz2 | patch -p1

for gz patch
gunzip -c /usr/src/patch.gz | patch -p1 --dry-run
gunzip -c /usr/src/patch.gz | patch -p1

6. configure kernel
make clean
make mrproper
cp /boot/config-`uname -r` ./.config
make menuconfig

7. build kernel
make rpm
if encounter problem "unknown option"
solution:
install rpm-build

src.rpm & rpm are created 

8. install kernel








